						<summary>

						

						<p>Stone lying on the bund of the tank.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1852 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated in the month of May in the year 1852 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This Telugu verse inscription records the rebuilding of the lake which was built by Gōṁpanavoḍiyalu.</p>						

						<p>It states that Nadi Varadarājaṁma got a portion of the lake being carefully rebuilt. The lake was completed with the money brought from Nēkhunāṁkhān, for the merit of the king. It mentions the names of Mahaṁmadu Agharapu Bāhubaluḍu, Engineer Major Ḍibeṭsu, Sundaramodalār, etc.</p>						

						</summary>
